  "prompt": "How much bandwidth per MH does scrypt mining use?",
  "response": "The bandwidth usage for scrypt mining can vary based on several factors, including the mining software being used, the specific implementation of the scrypt algorithm, and network conditions. However, scrypt mining generally does not consume a significant amount of bandwidth in relation to other activities, such as video streaming or file downloads.\n\nAs a rough estimate, scrypt mining might use about a few kilobytes per MH (megahash) per second. This is a very low figure, often cited as being around 1 to 3 KB per MH per second. Most of the data transferred consists of shares being submitted to the mining pool and the mining pool's response.\n\nKeep in mind, the exact bandwidth can depend on the efficiency of the mining pool, the frequency of share submissions, and network latency. To get the best idea of bandwidth use in your specific mining setup, monitoring your network traffic while mining would give you the most accurate results.",
